Intel’s latest Core Ultra desktop CPUs like the 9285K might be technically impressive, but almost no one is buying them. Linus digs into Amazon’s best sellers list and finds that most buyers still prefer older 12th and 13th gen chips, or have jumped to AMD entirely. Meanwhile, Intel is laying off staff, struggling to meet demand for older chips, and increasingly prioritizing mobile and server over enthusiast desktop. Has Arrow Lake already flopped?
